 113:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c **** /** @defgroup RCC_Exported_Functions_Group1 Initialization and de-initialization functions
 114:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****   *  @brief    Initialization and Configuration functions
 115:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****   *
 116:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****   @verbatim
 117:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****  ===============================================================================
 118:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            ##### Initialization and de-initialization functions #####
 119:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****  ===============================================================================
 120:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****     [..]
 121:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****       This section provides functions allowing to configure the internal and external oscillators
 122:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (HSE, HSI, LSE, CSI, LSI, PLL1, HSE CSS and MCOs) and the System busses clocks (SYSCLK, AHB, 
 123:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****        and APB3).
 124:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 125:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****     [..] Internal/external clock and PLL configuration
 126:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) HSI (high-speed internal): 64 MHz factory-trimmed RC used directly or through
 127:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              the PLL as System clock source.
 128:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 129:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (#) CSI is a low-power RC oscillator which can be used directly as system clock, periphera
 130:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              clock, or PLL input. But even with frequency calibration, is less accurate than an
 131:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              external crystal oscillator or ceramic resonator.
 132:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 133:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) LSI (low-speed internal): 32 KHz low consumption RC used as IWDG and/or RTC
 134:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              clock source.
 135:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 136:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) HSE (high-speed external): 4 to 48 MHz crystal oscillator used directly or
 137:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              through the PLL as System clock source. Can be used also optionally as RTC clock sourc
 138:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 139:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) LSE (low-speed external): 32.768 KHz oscillator used optionally as RTC clock source.
 140:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 141:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) PLL1 (clocked by HSI, HSE or CSI) providing up to three independent output clocks:
 142:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) The first output is used to generate the high speed system clock (up to 250MHz).
 143:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) The second output is used to generate the clock for the USB (48 MHz), the FDCAN1/2,
ARM GAS  C:\Users\DELL\AppData\Local\Temp\ccfPt8lb.s 			page 4


 144:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 the SPI1/2/3, the OCTOSPI, the RNG (<=48 MHz), the SDMMC1/2 and to generate an accu
 145:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 clock to achieve high-quality audio performance on SAI1/2 interface.
 146:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 147:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) PLL2 (clocked by HSI, HSE or CSI) providing up to three independent output clocks:
 148:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) The first output is used to generate the clock for the LPTIMs, the SPI1/2/3 and to 
 149:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 an accurate clock to achieve high-quality audio performance on SAI1/2 interface.
 150:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) The second output is used to generate the clock for USARTs, the UARTs, the LPUART1,
 151:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 the FDCAN1/2, the SPI4/5/6 and the USB.
 152:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) The third output is used to generate the clock the SDMMC1/2, the ADC/DAC, the I2C1/
 153:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 the I3C1/2 and the OCTOSPI.
 154:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 155:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) PLL3 (clocked by HSI , HSE or CSI) providing up to three independent output clocks:
 156:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) The first output is used to generate the clock for SPI1/2/3 and to generate an accu
 157:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 clock to achieve high-quality audio performance on SAI1/2 interface.
 158:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) The second  output is used to generate the clock for USARTs, the UARTs, the LPUART1
 159:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 the SPI4/5/6 and the USB.
 160:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) The third output is used to generate the clock for the I2Cs, the I3Cs and the LPTIM
 161:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 162:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) HSE CSS (HSE Clock Security System): once enabled, if a HSE clock failure occurs
 163:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****             (HSE used directly or through PLL1 as System clock source), the System clock
 164:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              is automatically switched to HSI and an interrupt is generated if enabled.
 165:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              The interrupt is linked to the Cortex-M33 NMI (Non-Maskable Interrupt)
 166:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              exception vector.
 167:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 168:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (#) MCO1 (micro controller clock output1), used to output HSI, LSE, HSE, PLL1(PLL1_Q)
 169:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              or HSI48 clock (through a configurable pre-scaler) on PA8 pin.
 170:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 171:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (#) MCO2 (micro controller clock output2), used to output HSE, PLL2(PLL2_P), SYSCLK,
